**Correctness — provider change doesn't sync `_configs` state**

`_setDefaultsForProvider` updates `_baseUrlController` and `_defaultModelController` but does not update `_configs[_activeConfigIndex]`. The `ChoiceChip` label in `_buildConfigSelector` reads from `_configs[index].defaultModel`, so after changing the provider the chip label retains the old model name until the user manually edits the model field.

Suggested fix — update `_configs` when the provider changes:
```dart
onChanged: (value) {
  if (value == null) return;
  setState(() {
    _provider = value;
    _setDefaultsForProvider(value);
    _configs[_activeConfigIndex] = _configs[_activeConfigIndex].copyWith(
      provider: value,
      baseUrl: _defaultBaseUrl(value),
      defaultModel: _defaultModel(value),
    );
  });
},
```
